8.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gdf1665702534898.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gdf1665702534898.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gdf1665702534898\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Hide the View by removing it from its parent element.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gdf1665702534898__topic_d127388e1_d127389e1_d127390e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gdf1665702534898__p_d127391e1_d127392e1_d127393e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">unifaceViewObject</var>.<span class=\"keyword apiname\">hide()</span>\n</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gdf1665702534898__section_w1373ab1b5b3_w1374ab1b5_w1375ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d831542e64\">Return Value</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">None</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gdf1665702534898__section_w1376ab1b5b5_w1377ab1b5_w1378ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d831542e73\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gdf1665702534898__p_d127403e1_d127404e1_d127405e1\">When a View is first created using\n               <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.Instance.createView</span>, it is automatically displayed in the\n            specified parent element. You can use <span class=\"keyword apiname\">hide()</span> to remove it from the\n            its parent element, but the View itself remains available. It can be shown again using\n               <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.View.show()</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"gdf1665702534898__note_a477938c745598891bbe27e5cc848485\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> This function does not work\n            with the default view that is automatically created by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">weblayout</span>\n            ProcScript command.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527805\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527805\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "hide() Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Hide the View by removing it from its parent element. unifaceViewObject . hide() Return Value None Description When a View is first created using uniface.Instance.createView , it is automatically displayed in the specified parent element. You can use hide() to remove it from the its parent element, but the View itself remains available. It can be shown again using uniface.View.show() . Note: This function does not work with the default view that is automatically created by the weblayout ProcScript command. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}